Preheat the oven to 200°C. Fill and boil your #kettle{}. Halve and peel the @red onion{1}. Chop each half into three pieces. Trim the @courgette{1}, then halve lengthways and chop into roughly 1cm wide 5cm long batons. Halve the @radishes{100}. Crumble the @feta cheese{100} into small pieces and set aside.

Pop the red onion, courgette and radishes on a large #baking tray{} in a single layer. Drizzle with @olive oil{for the veggies}, and sprinkle on the @chermoula spice mix{1}, season with @salt{} and @pepper{}. Toss to coat, then spread out and roast on the top shelf of your oven until golden, ~{20-25%minutes}.

> Use two baking trays if necessary, you want everything nicely spread out.

Pour the @water{240} for the bulgur wheat into a #saucepan{} with the @chicken stock powder{1} and bring to the boil. Stir in the @bulgur wheat{120}, bring back up to the boil and simmer for ~{1%minute}. Pop a lid on the pan and remove from the heat. Leave to the side for ~{12-15%minutes} or until ready to serve.

When the veg have been cooking for ~{10%minutes}, turn them and then pop the @salmon fillets{2} into the oven to roast for the remaining ~{10-15%minutes}. IMPORTANT: The salmon is cooked when opaque all the way through. Meanwhile, halve the @baby plum tomatoes{125} and pop them in a #bowl{}. Roughly chop the @flat leaf parsley{1}(roughly chopped). Add half of the parsley to the tomatoes along with the @red wine vinegar{12} and @olive oil{for the dressing}. Season with salt and pepper and mix together. Set aside.

Once the bulgar is cooked add the remaining chopped parsley and mix through. Season with salt and pepper to taste. Once your veg is cooked, remove from the oven.

Divide the bulgar between plates and top with equal portions of roasted veggies and tomato salad. Place the salmon fillet on top and finish off with a crumble of feta and enjoy!

> Step 2 MOD: If you've opted to get salmon instead of chicken, ignore the chicken cooking instructions in this step.

> Step 4 MOD: If you've got salmon, before you prep the tomatoes in the above step, pop the salmon on a lightly oiled baking tray and season with salt and pepper.

> Step 5 MOD: Ignore the chicken instruction above if you've got salmon.

> Step 6 MOD: Serve the salmon fillet on top of the roasted veg, bulgur and tomato salad. Sprinkle the feta on top.